Supreme Court, Appellate Term, June, 1902.

Before Freedman, P. J., Gildersleeve and MacLeán, JJ.

George Behsmann, Appellant, v. Gertrude R. Waldo, Respondent. Appeal from judgment of the General Term of the City Court affirming judgment for defendant entered upon the verdict of a jury and order denying plaintiff’s motion for a new trial. F. Herwig, for appellant. Jones & McCormick, for respondent. Judgment affirmed, with costs.

No opinion.
